    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.274749>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 6. Morphological structures in adult Multiquaestia. 1. Head in lateral view of Multiquaestia iringana n. sp. 2. Venation of M. albimaculana Karisch. 3. Dorsal view of male abdomen of M. iringana n. sp. showing hair-pencil from edge of hind wing to cover of raised scales on dorsal side of abdomen. 4. The same as 3, but with the pencil exposed and spread. 5. Slide mount of abdomen of male M. skulei n. sp. showing modified hair-scales on tergites 4 and 5. 6. Slide mount of abdomen of male M. iringana n. sp. showing coremata and structure of sternite 8 (S 8), tergum 8 (T 8) and intersegmental ventral sclerite (IS)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/274749/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

